[[:Iran–Israel proxy conflict]] → {{no redirect|Iran–Israel conflict}} – Proxy is way too specific and no longer accurate to describe even the recent escalation. Korean conflict is described as a proxy conflict now even though in the past there was fighting during the Korea  war. Same logic applies here. [[User:Awesome Aasim|Aasim]] ([[User_talk:Awesome Aasim|<ruby>話す<rp>（</rp><rt>はなす</rt><rp>）</rp></ruby>]]) 23:12, 14 June 2025 (UTC)
*'''Oppose'''. Using the same logic brought up in last year's [[Special:PermanentLink/1295600961#Requested_move_15_April_2024|exact same discussion]], this article covers the forty-years long proxy conflict between Iran and Israel that is ongoing to this day. Events from three days ago should not change this fact, and [[2024 Iran–Israel conflict|an article already exists]] covering the ''non-proxy'' conflict; if the current events do turn into a longer war, it of course will still be noted here but should have a separate article focusing entirely on it. Both sides are still using proxies throughout the middle east to exert influence over one another and that shows no signs of coming to an end. [[User:Yeoutie|Yeoutie]] ([[User talk:Yeoutie|talk]]) 01:31, 15 June 2025 (UTC)
*'''Support'''. This ''was'' a proxy conflict only. This is not a proxy conflict anymore: it is a full conflict, that ''started'' as a proxy conflict and escalated as a full conflict; the proxy conflict can now be read as a phase of a general conflict. --[[User:Cyclopia|<span style="font-size:small;color:seagreen">cyclopia</span>]][[User talk:Cyclopia|<span style="color:red"><sup>speak!</sup></span>]] 12:45, 15 June 2025 (UTC)
:'''Oppose… again.''' I was involved in a similar discussion last year and my opinion remains the same. Just because it’s escalated to a direct war, doesn’t mean the proxy war never happened. The articles about them deserve to remain separate. If there ab''absolutely has to'' be a rename, something like [[Prelude to the Israel-Iran War]] would be a more appropriate target. [[User:ZionniThePeruser|ZionniThePeruser]] ([[User talk:ZionniThePeruser|talk]]) 16:13, 15 June 2025 (UTC)
::I think the current name is much better. [[User:KiltedKangaroo|KiltedKangaroo]] ([[User talk:KiltedKangaroo|talk]]) 13:49, 17 June 2025 (UTC)
*'''Support''' but i would '''wait''' for [[Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Iran–Israel War]] to close [[User:Braganza|Braganza]] ([[User talk:Braganza|talk]]) 21:34, 16 June 2025 (UTC)
*'''Oppose'''. The proxy war is notable on its own, as the actual war is notable on its own. The difference between local non-Iranian forces and distant Iranian forces should remain. There has been several land wars between Israel and its neighbours. A land war between Israel and Iran has not happened. In the unlikely event of such, it would cross 900 km of Syria/Jordan and Iraq. [[User:TGCP|TGCP]] ([[User talk:TGCP|talk]]) 03:39, 17 June 2025 (UTC)

*'''Support''' as it's a clear conflict between them. [[User:AimanAbir18plus|AimanAbir18plus]] ([[User talk:AimanAbir18plus|talk]]) 10:40, 17 June 2025 (UTC)

